4 overcomes the cruelty that shuts me out 5 from the beautiful sheepfold where I slept as a lamb, 6 an enemy to the wolves that wage war on it;
7 with another voice now, with another fleece 8 I will return a poet, and at the font 9 of my baptism I will take the laurel wreath;
10 because it was in the faith, which makes 11 souls known to God, that I entered here, and then 12 Peter turned my face towards it.
